member.name: T:ZLDNN.Modules.DNNArticle.MetaWeblog.ModuleInfoStruct
member.summary: The concept of the module here is fluid and may not represent the actual module for the implementation of your provider. For example, with the Blog module, the moduleLevelId is actually set to the blogId. The purpose of this struct is to track units where items are aggregated. If your module doesn't have an object like this, then just return information related to modules to which the currently logged on user would have access to either insert, update or delete items.
